  "rationale": "<p>Choice A is correct. With angle Q right, PQ is adjacent to angle P, QR is opposite to angle P, and PR is the hypotenuse. cos P = PQ/PR = 3/5, so PQ = 3k and PR = 5k. By the Pythagorean theorem, QR\u00b2 = PR\u00b2 - PQ\u00b2 = 25k\u00b2 - 9k\u00b2 = 16k\u00b2, so QR = 4k = 100, giving k = 25. Therefore PQ = 75.</p><p>Choice B uses 3/5 \u00b7 100. Choice C equals QR. Choice D equals the hypotenuse 5k.</p>",
